14:46.000 --> 14:49.000
But all people are a little different.

14:49.000 --> 14:59.000
If we talk, again, about the effect of specialization, then, as well as the threshold of pain, the threshold of specialization for each of us will be different.

14:59.000 --> 15:08.000
For example, it is noted that in enterprises where watches are manually assembled, for example, in Switzerland or Japan,

15:08.000 --> 15:18.000
women's labor is used more advantageously, because, apparently, women are more patient, more inclined to perform repeated operations over and over again.

15:18.000 --> 15:24.000
For many years they were engaged in knitting, sewing, these are quite tedious activities.

15:24.000 --> 15:31.000
So, today, for each of our employees there is a threshold of specialization.

15:31.000 --> 15:39.000
And a manager who is attentive to his team must be sure to take this into account and be able to analyze.

15:39.000 --> 15:57.000
Another factor of influence, no less important, is what tasks, what structure of tasks we set for our subordinates, what is the content of these tasks, what levels of responsibility these tasks imply.

15:57.000 --> 16:16.000
Each task has its own motivating potential, so for each task that our subordinate performs, for each task, we must also take into account how much it can motivate our subordinate to effective and successful actions.

16:16.000 --> 16:24.000
And the last factor, the factor of influence, is the corporate culture of the company. What does corporate culture have to do with it?

16:24.000 --> 16:44.000
