28:48.000 --> 29:07.000
Now let's go back to the ground. Let's forget about the researchers who have been devoted to this topic for a long time and talk about specific tools that allow us to design the work of our subordinates.

29:08.000 --> 29:17.000
The first tool that managers talked about at the beginning of the 20th century was the expansion of work.

29:18.000 --> 29:37.000
Then, in the midst of the industrialization era, our industrial production used new technologies and tools every year, which seemed to allow enterprises to work more effectively, with more attachment.

29:38.000 --> 29:49.000
Nevertheless, the introduction of all these technical innovations resulted in the resistance of staff, strikes, and the number of mistakes made by subordinates increased.

29:50.000 --> 29:58.000
The trend of that time was that the specialization of each worker should be at the maximum level.

29:59.000 --> 30:07.000
Then managers decided that they should expand the work of Charlie Chaplin on the assembly line.

30:08.000 --> 30:17.000
He should not only tighten nuts, but also screw in screws and attach other things to our part.

30:18.000 --> 30:20.000
This is called the expansion of work.

30:21.000 --> 30:30.000
When we increase the number of operations performed by one worker due to similar operations that he performed earlier.

30:31.000 --> 30:42.000
For example, our secretary can only sort and distribute incoming messages, mail, e-mail, etc.

30:43.000 --> 30:50.000
We can expand his work by offering him to work with incoming messages.

30:51.000 --> 30:56.000
Or, for example, I will describe a rather real situation.

30:57.000 --> 31:04.000
In the 1990s, business related to the sale of air tickets abroad began to develop quite actively in Russia.

31:05.000 --> 31:15.000
The iron curtain has been dissolved, and therefore, Russians, for example, began their travel life in this period.

31:16.000 --> 31:23.000
That is why, for example, there were quite a lot of tourist agencies in Moscow that specialized in the sale of air tickets.

31:23.000 --> 31:36.000
Moreover, people came to work in them with a high education, a fairly wide view, simply because, as you know, at that time many state enterprises switched to business.

31:37.000 --> 31:45.000
And so they happily learned a new business, began to use the Western booking systems of air tickets, and they were able to work.

31:45.000 --> 31:48.000
And they made quite a few mistakes.

31:49.000 --> 31:57.000
But a year after one of such enterprises was formed, the management began to notice that the percentage of incorrectly issued air tickets was growing.

31:58.000 --> 32:10.000
Naturally, the management did not immediately guess what the matter was, blamed the workers in some way, fined them somewhere, but this did not lead to any positive results for the organization.

32:10.000 --> 32:26.000
And only an invited psychologist guessed that people with a fairly high level of education, who could do various things in this period, were a little tired of the functions they performed.

32:26.000 --> 32:43.000
Then the psychologist offered the manager, let's offer our consultants on air tickets to perform a number of other works that will be in the same area, but will differ from a simple sale ticket.

32:43.000 --> 32:58.000
They were offered, at that time the company already had the Internet, to consult with buyers in addition to what weather conditions are appropriate, finding the appropriate information.

32:58.000 --> 33:24.000
And if a Russian resident flies abroad, to Frankfurt or Düsseldorf, where there are very complex airports, it is difficult to understand, then the airport scheme should be printed out and the passenger should be consulted in detail in advance on how to behave if he needs to make a transfer.

33:24.000 --> 33:34.000
Strangely, the manager saw after a while that the number of errors was high enough, and in this company it decreased.

33:34.000 --> 33:51.000
Therefore, the expansion of the work can be used, but this tool does not always work, because many people can honor this increase in load when the task is basically the same, the level of responsibility is approximately the same.

33:51.000 --> 34:05.000
The feedback does not change. Therefore, I would consider this tool a little outdated and would not recommend using it, with the exception of a few.

34:05.000 --> 34:14.000
The next tool we will talk about is a very promising and interesting tool, in my opinion, it is the rotation of work.

34:14.000 --> 34:29.000
Again, if we turn to a primitive, but clear example of the production process, this is when workers exchange functions with each other for a certain period of time.

34:29.000 --> 34:35.000
For example, today I was tightening nuts, and my neighbor was screwing screws, and the next day we exchanged them.

34:35.000 --> 34:52.000
If we talk about other businesses, then in them the rotation of work allows not only to ensure the interoperability of employees, which is very important for production, but also to solve a number of other problems.

34:53.000 --> 35:03.000
The rotation allows you to effectively learn and improve the system of interaction and communication in the company.

35:03.000 --> 35:14.000
I will give another example. You probably know that very often the sales department employees conflict with the finance department.

35:14.000 --> 35:34.000
This is a typical situation for a Russian enterprise, because the task of the finance department is to correctly select and take into account all the primary payment documents, contracts and other documentation that allows the finance department to report to the tax service.

35:34.000 --> 35:55.000
And the sales department has a task to get as much money as possible from the client. Thus, the tasks are quite different, and the sales department is sometimes cool in relation to what documents the client should provide to ensure that the payment is correct.

35:56.000 --> 36:09.000
In one company, a sales department employee who had been working there for several years realized that he was tired of interacting with clients and wanted to change his job.

36:09.000 --> 36:25.000
But the climate in the company was comfortable enough for him, and he did not want to say goodbye to it. Therefore, he approached his manager and said, Ivan Petrovich, I can't do sales anymore, I would like to do something else.

36:25.000 --> 36:46.000
And then the wise manager said, okay, you work great with clients and you know what kind of documentation should be in this area. Maybe you will deal with the issues of managing the financial department for some time. We'll see, maybe you'll like it.

36:47.000 --> 37:09.000
